record_data.record_plain_text: 1. Availability Seller makes electric energy, capacity, and ancillary services available in the Central and Northeast Regions under this tariff to any purchaser, except as prohibited below. 2. Rates All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller. 3. Seller Category Seller is a Category 2 seller in the Central region and a Category 1 seller in the Northeast region, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a). 4. Compliance with Commission Regulations Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. 5. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority Seller has received waiver of: Subparts B and C of Part 35, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; Part 41, Part 101, and Part 141, except sections 141.14 and 141.15, and with the exception that waiver of the provisions of Part 101 that apply to hydropower licenses is not granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects; and received blanket approval under Part 34. Shelby County Energy Center, LLC, Docket No. ER16-517-000 (2016) (unpublished letter order). 6. Ancillary Services MISO: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to MISO. PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. Third Party Provider: Third-party ancillary services: Seller offers Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, Operating Reserve-Supplemental, and Primary Frequency Response. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e. where the entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider's OATT for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization.

record_data.record_plain_text:
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control From Generation Sources Service Seller provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service (“Reactive Supply Service”) from a facility located in Shelby County, Illinois (the “Shelby County Facility”). This tariff sets forth Seller’s revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Supply Service from the Shelby County Facility pursuant to the Transmission and Energy Markets Tariff of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc.
REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
Seller’s revenue requirement consists of the fixed annual revenue requirement as set forth below.
Fixed Annual Revenue Requirement:
Fixed Annual Revenue Requirement is $819,000.00.
Monthly Revenue Requirement is $68,250.00 (based on Fixed Annual Revenue Requirement divided by 12).
